@host = http://localhost:3000
@baseUrl = {{host}}/api/v1
@token = Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### ============================================
### CHAT MODULE - Messaging System
### ============================================

### CONVERSATIONS - List Conversations
GET {{baseUrl}}/chat/conversations?page=1&limit=20
Authorization: {{token}}

### CONVERSATIONS - Get Conversation
GET {{baseUrl}}/chat/conversations/:conversationId
Authorization: {{token}}

### CONVERSATIONS - Create Conversation
POST {{baseUrl}}/chat/conversations
Authorization: {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "participantIds": ["user-uuid-1", "user-uuid-2"],
  "topic": "Project Discussion",
  "type": "group"
}

### MESSAGES - Send Message
POST {{baseUrl}}/chat/conversations/:conversationId/messages
Authorization: {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "content": "This is a test message",
  "type": "text"
}

### MESSAGES - Get Messages
GET {{baseUrl}}/chat/conversations/:conversationId/messages?page=1&limit=50
Authorization: {{token}}

### SENTIMENT - Analyze Sentiment
GET {{baseUrl}}/chat/messages/:messageId/sentiment
Authorization: {{token}}

### SMART REPLIES - Get Smart Replies
GET {{baseUrl}}/chat/conversations/:conversationId/smart-replies
Authorization: {{token}}

### REACTIONS - Add Reaction
POST {{baseUrl}}/chat/messages/:messageId/reactions
Authorization: {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "emoji": "üëç"
}

### Notes:
### - All endpoints require authentication
### - Message types: text, image, file, system
### - Replace UUIDs with actual IDs from your database
